{"name":"Leviathan Effigy","size":"gargantuan","type":"elemental","tag":"primal","alignment":"chaotic evil","hitDice":"12","armorName":"natural armor","shieldBonus":0,"natArmorBonus":4,"otherArmorDesc":"12 (natural armor)","speed":"30","burrowSpeed":"0","climbSpeed":"0","flySpeed":"0","hover":true,"swimSpeed":"120","customHP":false,"customSpeed":false,"hpText":"135 (10d20 + 30)","speedDesc":"30 ft., swim 40 ft.","strPoints":"20","dexPoints":"16","conPoints":"10","intPoints":"6","wisPoints":"16","chaPoints":"16","blindsight":"0","blind":false,"darkvision":"0","tremorsense":"0","truesight":"0","telepathy":0,"cr":"8","customCr":"1/2 (100 XP)","customProf":2,"isLegendary":true,"legendariesDescription":"[MON] can take the following Legendary Actions. Each action can only be used once, at the end of another character's turn. These actions are available progressively, one per each round, and must be expended before the round ends.","isLair":false,"lairDescription":"When fighting inside its lair, the sahuagin can invoke the ambient magic to take lair actions. On initiative count 20 (losing initiative ties), the sahuagin can take one lair action to cause one of the following effects:","lairDescriptionEnd":"The sahuagin can't repeat an effect until they have all been used, and it can't use the same effect two rounds in a row.","isRegional":false,"regionalDescription":"The region containing the sahuagin's lair is warped by the creature's presence, which creates one or more of the following effects:","regionalDescriptionEnd":"If the sahuagin dies, the first two effects fade over the course of 3d10 days.","properties":[],"abilities":[{"name":"Ephemeral","desc":"[MON] doesn't need to breath and its movement is not impeded by difficult terrain."},{"name":"Serpentiform","desc":"[MON]'s body is 10 feet wide and 50 feet long. Each intermediate segment is 10 by 10 feet wide and must be contiguous to either another segment or [MON]'s head or its tail."},{"name":"Bound by water","desc":"[MON] can hover on ground but at the end of its turn all of its body parts must be within 30 ft. from any body of water."},{"name":"Incomplete summoning","desc":"At the beginning of the combat, [MON] can only move or perform Legendary Actions. This effect is lifted after performing Rejoining."}],"actions":[{"name":"Rising tides","desc":"As a Bonus Action, [MON] can rise the sea level. Choose any islet or shore: the water level rises by 5 ft. inward, causing the shore to be submerged. This action can only target one contiguous piece of land at a time, and cannot be used multiple times to further rise the sea level."},{"name":"Tail sweep","desc":"_**(Recharges 5-6)**_: [MON] makes a sweeping attack with its tail. Each creature in a 15 ft. cone must pass a DC [STR SAVE] DEX saving throw or suffer [4d6] bludgeoning damage and be pushed back by 15 ft. On a success, they suffer half as much damage and are not pushed back."},{"name":"Multiattack","desc":"[MON] makes three attacks: two with its bite and one with its scale darts."},{"name":"Bite (Head)","desc":"_Melee Weapon Attack:_ [STR ATK] to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. _Hit:_ [STR 1D6] piercing damage."},{"name":"Scale Darts (Tail)","desc":"_Ranged Weapon Attack:_ [STR ATK] to hit, range 60/120 ft., one target. _Hit:_ [STR 1D6] piercing damage."}],"reactions":[{"name":"One with the sea","desc":"[MON] can freely control water within 120 ft of its body. As a reaction whenever a creature becomes closer than 5 ft. to any free body of water (exclude those occupied by [MON]'s body), [MON] tries to grapple it. If it succeeds the target is restrained as tendrils of enchanted water envelope it.\n\nAt the beginning of the creature's turn, if it fails to escape, it gets dragged by 5 ft. closer to water. A creature that gets dragged under water, or is restrained under water, takes [STR 2d4] bludgeoning damage at the beginning of its turn. After 3 turns it starts suffocating, unless it can breathe under water.\n\nAs an action, another creature can disentangle the tendrils, freeing the target creature."}],"legendaries":[{"name":"1. Liquify","desc":"[MON] loses its corporeal form temporarily and disappears under water. While in this state, it cannot be targeted, suffer damage or perform any action."},{"name":"2. Rejoining","desc":"[MON] absorbs aether from its believers. Any follower of [MON] within 300 ft. is immediately killed: [MON] gains as many temporary hit points as the killed followers had, up to a maximum of 50. It then reemerges from any point of water, becomes targetable again and can now perform all of its actions."},{"name":"3. Spinning Dive","desc":"[MON] liquifies again. It immediately reappears from any point in water within 300 ft. and comes rushing towards another point in a straight line. Each creature in a 20 ft. wide line must make a DC [STR SAVE] DEX save or suffer [4d6] damage and be pushed back by 20 ft. On a save, they suffer half as much damage and are not pushed back."},{"name":"4. Tidal Wave","desc":"[MON] unleashes the power of the sea. Each creature within 120 ft. from [MON]'s head must pass a DC [WIS SAVE] WIS saving throw or gain one level of enthrallment. They must also pass a DC [STR SAVE] CON saving throw and suffer [5d6] cold damage on a fail, or half as much on a success."}],"lairs":[],"regionals":[],"sthrows":[{"name":"str","order":0},{"name":"wis","order":4}],"skills":[],"damagetypes":[{"name":"cold","note":" (Immune)","type":"i"}],"specialdamage":[{"name":"bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing from nonmagical attacks","note":" (Resistant)","type":"r"}],"conditions":[],"languages":[],"understandsBut":"","shortName":"Leviathan","doubleColumns":true,"separationPoint":1,"damage":[],"pluralName":"Leviathan"}